<h2 id="readme">README</h2>

<p>In <a href="https://blogs.loc.gov/law/2022/09/introducing-the-congress-gov-api/">October</a>, the Library of Congress published a Congress.gov application programming interface. Using this API, we created House of Representatives, Senate and member profiles pages on <a href="https://usa.govfresh.com">USA.GovFresh</a>.</p>

<h2 id="data">Data</h2>

<p>Data used for this project:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://home.dotgov.gov/data/">.gov domains</a> (Cybersecurity Infrastructure Security Agency)</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="repo">Repo</h2>

<p>Official repository:</p>

<ul>
  <li>/<a href="https://github.com/cisagov">cisagov</a>/<a href="https://github.com/cisagov/dotgov-data">dotgov-data</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="kudos">Kudos</h2>

<p>Big kudos to the Cybersecurity Infrastructure Security Agency for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Maintaining the .gov registry.</li>
  <li>Creating a public repository of the data.</li>
</ul>

